	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Jan 8th 11:22 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Jandon,<br>This is not a skill that you can increase.&nbsp;&nbsp;It stays at skill level 1 and will always do 1 point of damage.  This is not an offensive skill however, it is a defensive one.  The Slam skill is used for the purpose of interupting spell casters.  Next time you are engaged in combat with a spell casting mob, walk up to it and hit your slam hotkey as soon as you see the message that the mob &quot;begins to cast a spell&quot;.  If you are successful you will score 1 point of damage and will interupt the spell.  Unfortunately the refresh time on this skill seems to be just about 1 second slower than the recast time of the mob you are fighting so he it gets the spell off anyway.  This skill can be particularlly useful for interupting a healing mob when it is low health, stop his spell with a slam and finish him off before he can cast again.  Good luck.<br>&nbsp;<br>Baron Smokejaguar Yaxteel<br>Level 60 Barbarian Oracle<br>The Relentless<br>Cazic Thule</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
