	   <tr><td colspan=2>Poor hunting grounds? Bad lighting? Are you talking about Tox Forest? <br><br>Odus is a great place to hunt solo.(it's hard to get a group for some reason? at least on my server even though 20 people are in the zone.)<br><br>Warrens has great loot, as does Stonebrunt Mtns. You can hunt in the warrens into your mid twenties and then move to Stonebrunt and stay into your thirties! Only problem is as a Barbarain you'll have to run to Erudin to bank and sell, and you can become loaded with loot fast!<br><br>Yes the ship to Odus is safe, and no there is no &quot;fare&quot;. The boat ride is free! You may want to stay on the little island in Odus's Crossing killing Willowisps for awhile to get their Greater Light Stones, worth 5pp to PC's, 7-9pp to an NPC in North Karana. <br><br>I suggest you print out maps to the warrens, you can get maps at EQatlas.com<br><br>You'll need a map of Erudin, Toxulia(sp?) Forest, Paineel, the Warrens, and Stonbrunt Mountains.<br><br>Good hunting=)<br>Tondur<br>15 Shaman of the Tribunal<br>Torvonnilous<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
