	   <tr><td colspan=2>You could head over to Oasis.&nbsp;&nbsp;There are lots of caimans (kinda like little alligators) and crocodiles there which don't drop much loot, but do give a good amount of experience.  <br><br>To get there you head straight east from Qeynos into W. Karana, keep going east through N. Karana, High Pass Hold (get a guide-- it would be easier), east through Kithior Forest (go only during the daylight), through W. Commonlands, and enter into E. Commonlands.  Halfway through E.C. turn south and look for a tunnel (this is the area where lots of things get sold in most servers).  Head south in the tunnel, go into N. Ro, and head south again.  The next zone you come to will be Oasis.  From here you can eventually take a boat to Kunark, go to Freeport, head to Faydark or visit me in Grobb.<br><br>Granted, it is safer to get a teleport, but as long as you avoid creatures that will kill you you will be in a much better place to hunt.  Since you have SoW most baddies can't catch you anyhow.  <br><br>I would avoid Odus since the hunting grounds have always been poor, the lighting is bad, and Erudites are snobs.  However, the little island between Q and Odus is a terrific palce to hunt.  Just get on the boat in Q and hop off at the first place it docks.  There are lots of wisps to hunt (good plat), but *do not* touch the spiders.  Every spider will attack you if you kill one of their own.<br><br>Hope this helps!<br><br>--Pusbag Infection <br>&nbsp;<br>Emperor and Shamanic High Priest of the Trolls<br>"Worship Innoruuk, you worthless cattle!"<br></td></tr>
